,"pos":[6324,6370]},{"pos":[6384,6501],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601&gt;</ph> if your method has a return statement in which the operand has type <ph id=\"ph2\">`TResult`</ph>.","source":"<xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601> if your method has a return statement in which the operand has type `TResult`."},{"pos":[6515,6631],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task&gt;</ph> if your method has no return statement or has a return statement with no operand.","source":"<xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task> if your method has no return statement or has a return statement with no operand."},{"pos":[6645,6693],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`void`</ph> if you're writing an async event handler.","source":"`void` if you're writing an async event handler."},{"pos":[6705,6774],"content":"Any other type that has a <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetAwaiter`</ph> method (starting with C# 7.0).","source":"Any other type that has a `GetAwaiter` method (starting with C# 7.0)."},{"pos":[6783,6883],"content":"For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Return Types and Parameters<ept id=\"p1\">](#BKMK_ReturnTypesandParameters)</ept> section.","source":"For more information, see the [Return Types and Parameters](#BKMK_ReturnTypesandParameters) section."},{"content":"The method usually includes at least one <ph id=\"ph1\">`await`</ph> expression, which marks a point where the method can't continue until the awaited asynchronous operation is complete.","pos":[6893,7059],"source":"The method usually includes at least one `await` expression, which marks a point where the method can't continue until the awaited asynchronous operation is complete."},{"content":"In the meantime, the method is suspended, and control returns to the method's caller.","pos":[7060,7145]},{"content":"The next section of this topic illustrates what happens at the suspension point.","pos":[7146,7226]},{"content":"In async methods, you use the provided keywords and types to indicate what you want to do, and the compiler does the rest, including keeping track of what must happen when control returns to an await point in a suspended method.","pos":[7233,7461]},{"content":"Some routine processes, such as loops and exception handling, can be difficult to handle in traditional asynchronous code.","pos":[7462,7584]},{"content":"In an async method, you write these elements much as you would in a synchronous solution, and the problem is solved.","pos":[7585,7701]},{"pos":[7708,7940],"content":"For more information about asynchrony in previous versions of the .NET Framework, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>TPL and Traditional .NET Framework Asynchronous Programming<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../standard/parallel-programming/tpl-and-traditional-async-programming.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information about asynchrony in previous versions of the .NET Framework, see [TPL and Traditional .NET Framework Asynchronous Programming](../../../../standard/parallel-programming/tpl-and-traditional-async-programming.md)."},{"pos":[7949,8038],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_WhatHappensUnderstandinganAsyncMethod\"&gt;</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/a&gt;</ept> What happens in an async method","linkify":"<a name=\"BKMK_WhatHappensUnderstandinganAsyncMethod\"></a> What happens in an async method","source":"<a name=\"BKMK_WhatHappensUnderstandinganAsyncMethod\"></a> What happens in an async method"},{"content":"The most important thing to understand in asynchronous programming is how the control flow moves from method to method.","pos":[8042,8161]},{"content":"The following diagram leads you through the process.","pos":[8162,8214]},{"pos":[8221,8344],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">![</bpt>Trace an async program<ept id=\"p1\">]</ept><bpt id=\"p2\">(./media/task-asynchronous-programming-model/navigation-trace-async-program.png \"</bpt>NavigationTrace<ept id=\"p2\">\")</ept>","source":"![Trace an async program](./media/task-asynchronous-programming-model/navigation-trace-async-program.png \"NavigationTrace\")"},{"content":"The numbers in the diagram correspond to the following steps, initiated when the user clicks the \"start\" button.","pos":[8351,8463]},{"pos":[8471,8543],"content":"An event handler calls and awaits the  <ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> async method.","source":"An event handler calls and awaits the  `AccessTheWebAsync` async method."},{"pos":[8553,8763],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> creates an <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient&gt;</ph> instance and calls the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient.GetStringAsync%2A&gt;</ph> asynchronous method to download the contents of a website as a string.","source":"`AccessTheWebAsync` creates an <xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient> instance and calls the <xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient.GetStringAsync%2A> asynchronous method to download the contents of a website as a string."},{"content":"Something happens in <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetStringAsync`</ph> that suspends its progress.","pos":[8773,8838],"source":"Something happens in `GetStringAsync` that suspends its progress."},{"content":"Perhaps it must wait for a website to download or some other blocking activity.","pos":[8839,8918]},{"content":"To avoid blocking resources, <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetStringAsync`</ph> yields control to its caller, <ph id=\"ph2\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph>.","pos":[8919,9015],"source":" To avoid blocking resources, `GetStringAsync` yields control to its caller, `AccessTheWebAsync`."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`GetStringAsync`</ph> returns a <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601&gt;</ph>, where <ph id=\"ph3\">`TResult`</ph> is a string, and <ph id=\"ph4\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> assigns the task to the <ph id=\"ph5\">`getStringTask`</ph> variable.","pos":[9026,9195],"source":"`GetStringAsync` returns a <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task%601>, where `TResult` is a string, and `AccessTheWebAsync` assigns the task to the `getStringTask` variable."},{"content":"The task represents the ongoing process for the call to <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetStringAsync`</ph>, with a commitment to produce an actual string value when the work is complete.","pos":[9196,9348],"source":" The task represents the ongoing process for the call to `GetStringAsync`, with a commitment to produce an actual string value when the work is complete."},{"content":"Because <ph id=\"ph1\">`getStringTask`</ph> hasn't been awaited yet, <ph id=\"ph2\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> can continue with other work that doesn't depend on the final result from <ph id=\"ph3\">`GetStringAsync`</ph>.","pos":[9358,9518],"source":"Because `getStringTask` hasn't been awaited yet, `AccessTheWebAsync` can continue with other work that doesn't depend on the final result from `GetStringAsync`."},{"content":"That work is represented by a call to the synchronous method <ph id=\"ph1\">`DoIndependentWork`</ph>.","pos":[9519,9600],"source":" That work is represented by a call to the synchronous method `DoIndependentWork`."},{"pos":[9610,9699],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`DoIndependentWork`</ph> is a synchronous method that does its work and returns to its caller.","source":"`DoIndependentWork` is a synchronous method that does its work and returns to its caller."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> has run out of work that it can do without a result from <ph id=\"ph2\">`getStringTask`</ph>.","pos":[9709,9802],"source":"`AccessTheWebAsync` has run out of work that it can do without a result from `getStringTask`."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> next wants to calculate and return the length of the downloaded string, but the method can't calculate that value until the method has the string.","pos":[9803,9969],"source":"`AccessTheWebAsync` next wants to calculate and return the length of the downloaded string, but the method can't calculate that value until the method has the string."},{"content":"Therefore, <ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> uses an await operator to suspend its progress and to yield control to the method that called <ph id=\"ph2\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph>.","pos":[9980,10125],"source":"Therefore, `AccessTheWebAsync` uses an await operator to suspend its progress and to yield control to the method that called `AccessTheWebAsync`."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> returns a <ph id=\"ph2\">`Task&lt;int&gt;`</ph> to the caller.","pos":[10126,10182],"source":"`AccessTheWebAsync` returns a `Task<int>` to the caller."},{"content":"The task represents a promise to produce an integer result that's the length of the downloaded string.","pos":[10183,10285]},{"pos":[10297,10676],"content":"[!NOTE]\nIf `GetStringAsync` (and therefore `getStringTask`) completes before `AccessTheWebAsync` awaits it, control remains in `AccessTheWebAsync`. The expense of suspending and then returning to `AccessTheWebAsync` would be wasted if the called asynchronous process (`getStringTask`) has already completed and `AccessTheWebSync` doesn't have to wait for the final result.","leadings":["","    >  "],"nodes":[{"content":"If `GetStringAsync` (and therefore `getStringTask`) completes before `AccessTheWebAsync` awaits it, control remains in `AccessTheWebAsync`. The expense of suspending and then returning to `AccessTheWebAsync` would be wasted if the called asynchronous process (`getStringTask`) has already completed and `AccessTheWebSync` doesn't have to wait for the final result.","pos":[8,372],"nodes":[{"content":"If <ph id=\"ph1\">`GetStringAsync`</ph> (and therefore <ph id=\"ph2\">`getStringTask`</ph>) completes before <ph id=\"ph3\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph> awaits it, control remains in <ph id=\"ph4\">`AccessTheWebAsync`</ph>.","pos":[0,139],"source":"If `GetStringAsync` (and therefore `getStringTask`) completes before `AccessTheWebAsync` awaits it, control remains in `AccessTheWebAsync`."},{"content":"The expense of suspending and then returning to <ph id=\"ph1\">`AccessTheWebAsync`<